SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 38
By Hatcher
A RESOLUTION to honor Chief Roger Robinson on the occasion
of his retirement from the Alcoa Fire
Department.
WHEREAS, it is appropriate that we should honor those citizens who have performed
with uncommon devotion and enthusiasm in securing the safety of their community; and
WHEREAS, Roger Robinson is one such estimable individual, who served with
distinction for forty-five years as a member of the Alcoa Fire Department, including a seventeen-
year tenure as its chief, and recently embarked upon a much-deserved retirement; and
WHEREAS, an innovator in fire service, Chief Robinson planned and constructed a
training site where regional firefighters have honed and perfected their technique, ensuring the
greater safety and security of their fellow citizens; and
WHEREAS, under his leadership, the department received a Commission on Fire
Accreditation International (CFAI) accreditation in 2013, a recognition it has additionally
received in 2017 and 2023; and
WHEREAS, the tenure of Chief Robinson also saw the department earn an Insurance
Services Office (ISO) score of 1 in 2021, making Alcoa Fire Department one of only three
departments in the State to do so and one of only 120 departments in the country that are CFAI-
accredited with an ISO 1; and
WHEREAS, a leader among leaders, Chief Robinson served on the Board of Directors
of the Tennessee Fire Chief's Association and became its president in 2014; and
WHEREAS, Chief Roger Robinson exemplifies the spirit and allegiance to family and
community that are characteristic of a true Tennessean; and
